observations.recommendation:
Therefore, we recommend that the Municipal Mayor shall create an inventory committee that will facilitate the conduct of the physical count of its Property, Plant and Equipment (PPE) as provided under Commission on Audit (COA) Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020. Also, to instruct the following in relation thereto, to wit:
1.) Inventory Committee shall prepare the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE), in compliance with Section 124 of the Manual on the New Government Accounting System (MNGAS) for Local Government Units (LGUs), Volume I;
2.) General Services Officer shall maintain and update her property cards per category of property, plant and equipment, pursuant to Section 119 of MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I;
3.) Municipal Accountant shall maintain and update her property ledger cards per category of property, plant and equipment, pursuant to Section 120 of MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I; and
4.) Ensure that the General Services Office and Municipal Accountant shall reconcile their property cards and property ledger cards, respectively.
